name: r-norm
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0-10.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-norm
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/norm_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/norm/norm_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4384791af74c1008238f036abe0dda4b4048b9700cc4acd7b45025598fd20cc7

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('fortran') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_fortran') }}  # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('norm')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('norm')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=norm
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: An integrated set of functions for the analysis of multivariate normal datasets with
    missing values, including implementation of the EM algorithm, data augmentation,
    and multiple imputation.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2
  
extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
